–	*John P. Burns, “The Chinese Communist Party’s Nomenklatura System as a Leadership Selection Mechanism: An Evaluation,” in Kjeld Erik Brodsgaard and Zheng Yongnian (eds.), The Chinese Communist Party in Reform (New York: Routledge, 2006), pp. 33-58.
–	Andrew G. Walder, “The Party Elite and China’s Trajectory of Change,” in Brodsgaard and Zheng, pp. 15-22.
Week #4 (3/12):  Central-Local Relations (I): General Perspectives and Personnel Management
–	Susan Shirk, The Political Logic of Economic Reform in China (Berkeley: University of California Press, 1993), Chapters 1, 3, 4, pp.1-22, 55-91.
–	Jae Ho Chung, “Studies of Central-Provincial Relations in the People’s Republic of China: A Mid-term Appraisal,” China Quarterly 142 (1995). （臺大圖書館電子期刊全文電子檔）
